  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fungal infections have increased over the last two decades, largely because of the increasing
      size of the population at risk, including patients who are immunocompromised, broad-spectrum
      antibiotics and intravascular catheter users. Essential oils and other extracts of plants
      have evoked interest as sources of natural products. They have been shown to possess
      antibacterial, antifungal, antiviral, insecticidal and antioxidant properties. To the best of
      our knowledge, no study has examined the efficacy of cumin seed extract on relieving
      vulvovaginal candidiasis in vivo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
