  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Women were 18-49 years old and were married;

          2. They had not used antibiotics, immunosuppressive drugs, or vaginal drugs 14 days
             before the study;

          3. They did not suffer from trichomonal vaginitis, bacterial vaginitis, or cervicitis
             based on direct smear;

          4. Candidiasis culture was in agreement with clinical symptoms and patient's complaints.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pregnant and lactating women;

          2. Those who had abnormal uterine bleeding;

          3. Women with diabetes or autoimmune diseases;

          4. Women refuse to participate in the study.
      </textblock>
